Patricia Brooks https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patricia_Brooks 0 Patricia Brooks (November 7, 1937 – January 22, 1993), was a lyric soprano, actress, and opera singer, who performed primarily with the New York City Opera. She was known for her acting ability as much as for her voice.
